		<blockquote class="quote-2">
			<p>&ldquo;<a href="/article/4397">You Always Call on a Sunday</a>,&rdquo; by Jackie Shannon Hollis [March 2010], is exactly why I love this magazine. There is no hidden meaning in her story at all, just the truth as it should be written: graphic, heartbreaking, and real. That essay was straight from the heart, and I understood every last bit of it.</p>
							<p class="quote-2-author">Shelly Nelson<br>Berwick, Iowa</p>
